<item>
            <title>[SPARK-29236] Access &apos;executorDataMap&apos; out of &apos;DriverEndpoint&apos; should be protected by lock</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SPARK-29236</link>
                <project id="12315420" key="SPARK">Spark</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Just as the comments:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;// Accessing `executorDataMap` in `DriverEndpoint.receive/receiveAndReply` doesn&apos;t need any&lt;br/&gt;
// protection. But accessing `executorDataMap` out of `DriverEndpoint.receive/receiveAndReply`&lt;br/&gt;
// must be protected by `CoarseGrainedSchedulerBackend.this`. Besides, `executorDataMap` should&lt;br/&gt;
// only be modified in `DriverEndpoint.receive/receiveAndReply` with protection by&lt;br/&gt;
// `CoarseGrainedSchedulerBackend.this`.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;`executorDataMap` is not threadsafe, it should be protected by lock when accessing it out of `DriverEndpoint`&lt;/p&gt;</description>
